  "commentary": "**Dealer Hedging Commentary:**\n\nWith SPX at 6576 sitting above the GEX flip at 6559 but below the massive 27B gamma wall at 6580, dealers are positioned to sell any push higher into that resistance level while providing buying support on dips back toward the flip. The PIN regime with heavy positive gamma concentration between 6580-6600 creates a strong ceiling effect, suggesting price action will likely grind sideways to lower with mean reversion bias. Watch 6580 as the critical resistance where dealer selling intensifies and 6559 as the pivot—break below flips dealers to short gamma and accelerates downside momentum toward the 6500 negative gamma zone.",
